caption: A peaceful place hidden in Paris. Just for a moment…

Quiet, unassuming garden area in which to take a break from the busy streets of the Marais. Benches surround the perimeter so you can rest your weary dogs before heading back out. I'm very happy I discovered this little gem.
Hidden gem with some beautiful rose varietals
Lovely tiny hidden Park 2 steps from Picasso museum
Beautiful hidden garden, well maintained a real gem worth the visit!
A hidden quite garden in the heart of Paris. A great place to take a rest and some lunch.
Perfect place to relax and read a book - so calm, even though it’s close to the tourist area.
Small but cozy place!
A little public piece of silence and roses in the hiding of private houses
very nice day, weather was wonderful to be here
Quiet place, excellent for relax!
Lovely parc and quite in Paris
Good place to visit if in Paris.

Magnificent square with trees and flowers, very well maintained. Protected from noise, it is ideal for a break. It includes a small play area for children. Lines of trees, geometric flowerbeds surrounded by paths and stone benches characterize this garden. Added to these charms is the view of the facade of the Grand Veneur mansion. This historic monument built in the 17th century was acquired and transformed in 1734 by Vincent Hennequin, Marquis d'Ecquevilly, captain general of the king's hunting expedition - in other words of his hunting crew - at the origin of the exterior decorations celebrating his activity. The name of the square associates Grand Veneur with Saint-Gilles, named after the neighboring street of the same name. This garden pays homage to Pauline Roland (1805- 1852), feminist, close to Georges Sand, teacher, writer and journalist.
A nice place to relax. Set up as a rose garden between the houses and well maintained. You just have to know where he is!

What a great discovery! This pretty garden is nestled in a very discreet corner of the Marais. Little haven of peace, where that day, a couple played and sang Joao Gilberto... Magnificent! Delicious afternoon...

This magnificent square (like all the others) is a poor reflection of the Parisian microcosm: it well sums up the “no” of knowing how to live together of the neighboring owner who wants peace, of the mother of the family who wants space, the dog owner who wants greenery, the onlooker who can pee in peace (or more) against the wall, the young people who come to squat and smoke the lawn, and the one who comes to read in peace. Neighbors managed to ban access to the dogs by tirelessly calling the police. The city installed children's games to endorse the ban. Sound games have been installed so they continue to call the police for the shrill sounds. Human piss and droppings can remain peacefully along the wall...they don't make any noise.

#Discreet and peaceful rose garden in the heart of Paris. Various varieties form four beds with lawns. Pay attention to the detail of each specimen. The plantations are sublime, of great research and great delicacy.
A magical place in the center of the marsh. The square is tiny, a pocket square, but it is absolutely calm. In fine weather it's a pleasure to go there and enjoy the sun, provided you have space!
Good sunny hiding place among the rose bushes for sunbathing, reading or picnicking. A haven of peace in the middle of the hustle and bustle.
It is a very pleasant and very quiet place located in the heart of Paris.
Very small, very quiet garden ideal for lunch
Small park of an old mansion among the surrounding buildings

Trash bin installed in the perspective of the fountain, tagged and leprous walls, shabby lawns, torn out crossbars. According to the guides, one of the most beautiful public squares in Paris but abandoned for years by the socialist town hall of the 3rd.  We will no longer vote for them!
Small, quiet garden with superb rose bushes. With a small fountain for drinking, very practical
Very quiet and a little "hidden" park. There are no sounds of children, only dogs with their owners. Very beautiful vegetation and an ideal setting for quietly sunbathing.
Magnificent little garden hidden in a residence. The mansion provides a perfect setting.
Really quiet, lots of space and benches but no toilets!
A hidden square which must have been the garden of a private mansion on rue de Turenne with magnificent climbing rose bushes
Well hidden place, beautifully arranged with beautiful rose bushes.
Square hidden in the marsh, so there are very few people there. It is very small, benches allow you to relax given the calm that reigns there. The square is also very well maintained.

Small secret garden, very picturesque, hidden in a courtyard of a private residence. Very calm and soothing, there are never too many people. It's easy to find somewhere to sit even on weekends when the weather is nice.
Magnificent little square, calm and quiet. It is very well hidden and is only frequented by connoisseurs and regulars. You can't see it from the street.
A hidden and typical place in the Marais... ideal for a break... somewhere else.

A small green space of barely 1000 m2, close to Place des Vosges, surrounded by two beautiful mansions, four small lawns in the middle of a beautiful rose garden, a few benches, absolute calm just a stone's throw from Boulevard Beaumarchais!
Very pretty in summer, flowers everywhere. A few benches, a bit of lawn, but no children's play area or place for football, etc.

Small, friendly and quiet park. Negative point, it needs some small improvements on one side because one wall is tagged and spoils the appeal of this peaceful little corner. This place is not made for children.
Very beautiful garden but has become a giant urinal for all the dogs in the neighborhood. Unfortunately not recommended for young children who would like to relax in the grass...
